PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772658365
OL,3,CHow to see tonight's worm moon in the
OL,4,CUK, as blood moon visible around the
OL,5,Cworld
OL,7,FSuch eclipses only occur every 18
OL,8,Fmonths to three years, with the next
OL,9,Fone expected to appear on New Year's
OL,10,FEve 2028.
OL,12,FA partial lunar eclipse will also be
OL,13,Fvisible on August 28 from parts of
OL,14,FAfrica, the East Pacific, the Americas
OL,15,Fand Europe, according to Nasa.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/5
